p: DENV2 QML16 was detected in legs and wings as early as 7 dpi while QML22 was not detected in these tissues until 10 dpi. Furthermore, QML22 disseminated to legs and wings in fewer mosquitoes that QML16 and virus grew to lower titres than QML16 at 7 and 10 dpi (Fig. 1a, b; χ 2 = 27.47, df = 1, P < 0.001). However, QML22 reached similar titers to QML16 in legs and wings by 14 dpi (Unpaired t-test, P = 0.0988, Fig. 1b).
